Japanese Prime Minister Shinzo Abe told China&#8217;s top diplomat on Wednesday that he would like to work with China to try to rein in North Korea&#8217;s nuclear and missile programmes.&#8220;To resolve this problem peacefully, we would like to work with China, which has strong influence (over North Korea),&#8221; Abe said at the outset of a meeting with Yang Jiechi.In return, Yang told Abe that he hoped all parties play a constructive role in resolving the issue.-Reuters